         <abstract>
            <p>An efficient method is given for obtaining the volume of a pyramid of species $n - 2$ whose base is a convex polygon. The pyramid is "transformed" into a simplex whose volume is computed directly. A refinement is provided to the Cohen-Hickey method for determining volumes of convex polyhedra.</p>
          </abstract>
